  "raw": {
    "citation": "Ogusu 2014 25372290",
    "population": "--PK-- N: 237 (Japanese) Sex: m=137, f=100 Age: 17.2±8.3 (2.2-52.2) WT: 48.8±20.9 (9.6-120.5) --PD— N: 169 (Japanese) Sex: m=102, f=67 Age: 18.0±7.8 (3.0 -52.2) WT: 51.0±20.1 (13.0-120.5)",
    "model_type": "PK PKPD",
    "objective": "“…to evaluate the impact of the most common and potentially functional polymorphisms in three antioxidant enzyme genes, i.e. SOD2, GSTM1 and GSTT1, on the relationship between the VPA exposure and the risk of c-GT elevation during long-term VPA therapy.”",
    "covariates": "Tested: SEX, AGE, WT, DVPA, genotype(CYP2C9, CYP2C19), comedication (CBZ, PHT, PHB,CLB) Included: DOSE, SEX, CBS, PHB, PHT, CLB --PD— Tested: AGE, SEX, WT, daily dose VPA, duration VPA, genotype (CYP2C19, SOD2, GSTM1, GSTT1), intellectual disability, comedication. Included: genotype (SOD2 Val/Val), intellectual disability.",
    "observations": "--PK-- The PK model represented PK of VPA and relation with VPA exposure and y-GT elevation. The variability is very small but goodness-of-fit plots added as supporting information. Final model reduced residual error by 17.9%. DDVPA significantly influenced Vd/F and CL of VPA. SEX(female), comedication (CBZ, PHB, PHT, CLB) significantly decreased objective function values of CL Genotypes (CYP2C9, CYP2C19) did not influence CL Limitation in study; could not determine standard error of PK parameters. --PD-- PK-PD models indicates that risk of γ-GT elevation is significantly related to VPA exposure. The risk of γ-GT elevation is described by a logistic model.",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "--PK-- 1 compartment model, first-order absorption and elimination --PD-- Logit regression of probability of attaining more than 50% reduction in seizure frequency",
    "equations": "—PK— CL=theta1*((DOSE/1000)**theta2)*(theta3**SEX)*(theta4**CBZ)*(theta5**PHB)*(theta6**PHT)*(theta7**CLBZ)* exp(eta1) V = theta8*((DOSE/1000)**theta9)* exp(eta2) KA= theta10* exp(eta3) ALAG1= theta11 * exp(eta4) Cobs=Cipred*(1+eps1) DOSE: daily VPA dose in mg/day SEX: Gender (1: female, 0:male) CBZ: comedication with carbamazepine (1: yes, 0: no) PHT: comedication with phenytoin (1: yes, 0: no) PHB: comedication with phenobarbital (1: yes, 0: no) CLBZ: comedication with clobazam (1: yes, 0: no) —PD— Logit(Pr)=log(Pr/(1-Pr)=theta1 + (theta2**INDI) + (theta3**GEN) + (DOSE**theta4) *AUC+ exp(eta1) AUC: individual AUC of VPA simulated by PK analyses INDI: intellectual disability of patient (1: yes, 0: no) GEN: genotype (1: SOD2Val/Val genotype, 0:SOD2 Val/Ala or Ala/Ala genotype) DOSE: daily VPA dose in mg/day",
    "parameter_values": "-- PK -- theta1= 0.559 theta2= 0.596 theta3= 0.917 theta4= 1.19 theta5= 1.12 theta6= 1.43 theta7= 0.906 theta8= 21.4 theta9= 1.52 theta10= 0.109 theta11= 3.00 omega1= 0.0587 omega2=1.83*10e-07 omega3=7.77*10e-07 omega4=4.48*10e-09 sigma1= 0.0617 --PD-- theta1= -6.63 theta2= 3.62 theta3= 1.96 theta4= 1.55 omega1= 12.3",
    "validation": "Yes (bootstrap of 1000) / No"
